&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We’re Hiring: Manager, Regional Renewals at Minitab&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Location: State College, PA, Remote in PA or our Chicago, IL office (Hybrid).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a strategic, people-first leader to build and scale a high-performing Renewals team within our Direct Sales organization. This is a unique opportunity to combine frontline leadership with hands-on deal strategy—driving predictable renewal outcomes, maximizing multi-year revenue, and reducing churn risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;br&gt;• Lead, coach, and develop a team of Renewals Specialists to exceed targets and grow their careers&lt;br&gt;• Drive a value-based renewal motion that improves GRR and NRR&lt;br&gt;• Partner cross-functionally with Sales, Customer Success, Finance, and Field Operations&lt;br&gt;• Own renewal execution excellence—from pipeline hygiene to forecasting accuracy&lt;br&gt;• Identify opportunities to scale processes, improve efficiency, and elevate team performance&lt;br&gt;• Step into complex, high-risk renewals to secure the best outcomes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who brings:&lt;br&gt;✔ 6+ years in renewals, sales, or account management (B2B SaaS/enterprise software)&lt;br&gt;✔ 4+ years of proven success leading teams as a people manager or team leader and driving retention metrics (GRR/NRR)&lt;br&gt;✔ Strong commercial acumen and negotiation skills&lt;br&gt;✔ A passion for coaching, developing talent, and building scalable processes&lt;br&gt;✔ The ability to influence cross-functional partners and lead through change&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re energized by building teams, driving results, and shaping the future of renewals, we’d love to connect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This&amp;nbsp;position&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;ineligible for visa sponsorship.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;To be&amp;nbsp;considered for this&amp;nbsp;role, you must be&amp;nbsp;legally authorized to work in the&amp;nbsp;United States and&amp;nbsp;not&amp;nbsp;require&amp;nbsp;sponsorship&amp;nbsp;for employment now or in&amp;nbsp;the future.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HEALTH INSURANCE&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp; Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance is provided at no cost for full-time employees upon date of hire. Low co-pay pharmacy benefit and affordable family coverage plan is available. Short and Long Term Disability is fully paid by Minitab. Employee Assistance Program (EAP) - Provides guidance for personal issue and information on other Work Life Matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIFE INSURANCE&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp; Group Term Life Insurance is provided at no cost for full-time employees at three times employee base salary. Minitab provides eligible employees the opportunity to purchase Voluntary Life Insurance for themselves and eligible dependents at affordable rates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RETIREMENT PLANNING:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; A 401k Retirement Plan with T. Rowe Price is provided with eligible employee contribution immediately. Minitab will match dollar for dollar up to the first 6% of employee’s contribution. Employees are fully vested in the Minitab, LLC 401(k) Retirement Plan upon date of hire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PAID TIME OFF&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp; Paid holidays, as well as 4 weeks of annual paid time off are provided. The annual paid time off increases one week every five years.&lt;/p&gt;
